---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Nivedita Pandey">
  <article class="about">
    <h1>About</h1>
    
    <section class="bio">
      <h2>Bio</h2>
      <p>
        I am a strategist and operator with 16+ years of international experience across the US, UK, Singapore, and India. 
        My work spans digital innovation, go-to-market execution, and cross-border ecosystem development—with a focus on 
        emerging technologies, institutional adoption, and public-private partnerships.
      </p>
      <p>
        I hold an MBA from Wharton and degrees in computer science and social impact. My career includes scaling Microsoft's 
        PE/VC partnerships vertical across APAC to $130M, serving as a Prime Minister's Fellow on Digital Payments and Digital 
        Public Infrastructure, and advising the Reserve Bank Innovation Hub on AI governance and DPI strategy.
      </p>
      <p>
        I currently run Dendrons.ai, an Applied AI Innovation Studio selected for Antler Singapore and Google Cloud for Startups. 
        I also serve as Managing Director - Asia for Wharton Alumni Angels and lead SkillAI.academy, a training brand focused on 
        AI governance and applied AI for institutions.
      </p>
    </section>
    
    <section class="work-on" id="work">
      <h2>What I Work On</h2>
      <p>
        My work sits at the intersection of three domains:
      </p>
      <ul class="work-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Digital Innovation:</strong> Product strategy for emerging technologies, with recent focus on AI governance, 
          digital public infrastructure, and healthcare coordination platforms.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Go-to-Market & Scale:</strong> Growth strategies, partnership development, and institutional sales—particularly 
          in technology adoption by governments, financial institutions, and enterprise.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Cross-Border Ecosystems:</strong> Building partnerships and market entry strategies across Asia-Pacific, 
          connecting innovation ecosystems between India, Singapore, and global markets.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    
    <section class="problems" id="problems">
      <h2>Problems I'm Working On</h2>
      <div class="problems-list">
        <div class="problem-item">
          <h3>Speech AI for Healthcare Access</h3>
          <p>
            How can voice-based AI interfaces improve healthcare access in low-literacy populations? What does responsible 
            deployment look like when patient data meets conversational AI?
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="problem-item">
          <h3>Institutional Adoption of AI</h3>
          <p>
            How do governments and regulated institutions build capacity for AI adoption—not just technical training, but 
            organizational readiness, governance frameworks, and change management?
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="problem-item">
          <h3>Digital Public Infrastructure Ecosystems</h3>
          <p>
            What makes DPI successful beyond the technology layer? How do you design for ecosystem participation, sustained 
            innovation, and equitable value distribution?
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="problem-item">
          <h3>NRI Healthcare Coordination</h3>
          <p>
            How can NRI families manage elderly parents' healthcare across fragmented providers in India? What's the right 
            balance between technology coordination and human care?
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <p class="problems-footer">
        If you are working on similar problems, I'd be interested to hear from you. 
        <a href="/contact">Get in touch.</a>
      </p>
    </section>
    
    <section class="beyond" id="beyond">
      <h2>Beyond Work</h2>
      <p>
        Outside of professional work, I have several deep interests that shape how I think and live.
      </p>
      
      <div class="beyond-grid">
        <div class="beyond-item">
          <h3>Animals & Rescue</h3>
          <p>
            I have a profound connection with animals, particularly cats. I support animal rescue work and believe in the 
            responsibility we have toward creatures who cannot advocate for themselves.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="beyond-item">
          <h3>Meditation & Spirituality</h3>
          <p>
            I maintain a serious engagement with Vedic astrology, the Ramcharitmanas, and meditation practices. These aren't 
            casual interests—they're frameworks I use to understand purpose, time, and uncertainty.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="beyond-item">
          <h3>Cooking & Food</h3>
          <p>
            I find deep satisfaction in cooking—the precision, the sensory engagement, and the act of creating something 
            nourishing. It's a grounding practice that connects to culture, memory, and care.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="beyond-item">
          <h3>Travel & Curiosity</h3>
          <p>
            I've lived and worked across multiple continents, and I'm endlessly curious about how systems, cultures, and 
            institutions work differently across contexts. Travel is less about tourism and more about pattern recognition.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: 750px;
  }
  
  .about h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  
  .about section {
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  
  .about section:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }
  
  .about h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  
  .about h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  
  .about p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .about p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  
  .work-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .work-list li {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
  
  .work-list strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  
  .problems-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  
  .problem-item {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  
  .problem-item h3 {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
  }
  
  .problem-item p {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  
  .problems-footer {
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
  }
  
  .beyond-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .beyond-item h3 {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  
  .beyond-item p {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
